<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-25T22:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-25T22:36:00-05:00" n="1087" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1087">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3721.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-25T21:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 25, 1912—9 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>A British war vessel will go to Mexican Pacific coast to aid British
                            colonists. This will probably be the signal for visits on both sides by
                            other nations.</p>
                        <p>Isthmus situation bad; also Oaxaca. Consul at Saltillo reports capture of
                            Cuatro Cienegas by rebels. General situation the same, with signs of
                            unrest in this city.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>